This paper discusses a methodology for designing experiments to compare the performance of optimization algorithms, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on statistical power and accuracy, which are important considerations in experimental design and analysis, and are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), data science (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical application of the proposed methodology, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
